
1. Getting Git (for server and client 1 and 2)
 $ apt-get -y install git
 $ git clone https://github.com/lukasp2/system-administration.git

2. Execute the server script (on the server)
 $ chmod +x server.sh
 $ ./server.sh
 
3. Execute the router and client script (on router and client 1 and 2)
 $ chmod +x router_and_clients.sh
 $ ./router_and_clients.sh
 
4. Run the tests
 $ dig dons.com
 $ dig -x 10.0.0.2
 $ dig +short @dons.com porttest.dns-oarc.net TXT = GREAT

Check the DNS configuration files with commands:
 $ named-checkconf /etc/bind/named.conf
 $ named-checkconf /etc/bind/named.conf.local
if the above commands returns nothing, it means DNS configuration is valid.

Check the zone files using commands:
 $ named-checkzone dons.com /etc/bind/for.dons.com
 $ named-checkzone dons.com /etc/bind/rev.dons.com
these commands should return two lines, the last one "OK"

.. done

reference website:
https://www.fosslinux.com/7631/how-to-install-and-configure-dns-on-ubuntu.htm
